<Review ID>3739743
<Product Name>Cowon D2 4GB Portable Media Player (Black)
<Title>Great MP3 Player
<Date>Sun Dec 09 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>The versatility of this model is great. The touch-screen will not appeal to all users but I find it extremely easy to use. Speaking for myself I love it.  Sound quality is among the best I have experienced. There are dozens of user selectable settings to tailor the sound to your personal taste. This unit works well with Windows Media Player. I did not care for the bundeled software.  I love the built-in SD card reader. The images display beautifully but high-res take a few seconds to fully render. Zoom and pan work well (very logical functionality) but again they take a moment to render.  Battery life is incredible. The battery will last more than 45 hours under heavy use.   Playing video requires some determination because they must be the right resolution or they will not play. This is my only complaint of this unit - but with only 4gb of storage this unit was clearly not intended to be a serious video player. For that reason I tend to largely dismiss this minor shortcoming - but potential buyer should understand this limitation.   Last but not least you're not tied to the restrictive / proprietary formats that Apple / Mac force you to go with. I hate the proprietary nonsense.  
