<Content>D2 is in a class of its own; it doesn't compare with any of the other popular brand Personal Media Players (PMP).  PROS: . Loud and crystal clear sound with way too many options to make it sound the way you like your music, e.g. Graphic Equalizer with several settings, EQ filter, Mach Bass, BBE, Surround Sound (fake), Stereo Enhancement, etc.   . Solid build quality. . TV Out and great video . Non-proprietary USB port for PC connection and charging.   . Downloadable Flash applications. . Fully customizable User Interface. . Multiple supported audio formats. . SD card expandability.  CONS: None.  I would have however liked a removable belt clip.  I use it with decent JLabs JBuds earphones (~$20).  I can't imagine how great D2 will sound with even better earphones.  If you are looking at this review, click on the Add to Cart button because you really can't go wrong with this little gadget.  I did a lot of research and tested some brand name players, but finally settled for this one.  The two players that made it to my short list included D2 and the iRiver Clix.  I haven't tried the Clix yet, but dropped it because of it inability to support expansion.  After using D2 for a few days, I am proud to have made the right decision.   
